This is a view from the outside of the peristyle.

A close up of the statue to the right of the arch is visible in Art &amp; Architecture of the Women's Building, <a href="http://digital.library.upenn.edu/women/elliott/art/art.html">1894 edition</a> page <a href="http://digital.library.upenn.edu/women/elliott/art/254-150.jpeg">254</a>.  It names the statue &quot;The Genius of Discovery&quot;, by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bela_Pratt">Bela L Pratt</a> of New York.

The bottom of the tablet behind the statue can be read, last three lines &quot;... conscience is my scepter and law my sword.&quot;
